inn1.comm: full and swinging in first up, but the line was down leg and he nudges it behind square
he went for it against Wade, he went for the yorker first ball, but it came out as a low full toss on middle and off, Wade turns it softly on the leg side
full delivery this time, inward movement into the left-hander, but again down leg, and tucked away to fine leg
the line is a tad better this time, the length is full, it swings in to the left hander, he takes it on the pad as he misses with the flick, going down leg easily
he is consistently going for the full inswinging delivery, this one is too full, too much on leg, and this time Warner gets enough bat on it to send it through square leg to the boundary
he tries to take on the pitched up delivery and launch it down the ground, but the inward shape means he gets an inside edge on to pad
completely different to Malinga, starts on a good length and moves it off the pitch across the left-hander who dabs it towards second slip
some bounce from just short of a length, but the line is down leg, and he takes a hand off the bat as he jabs it away
angles it across on a length, pushed towards covers
fine stroke, purposeful stride forward from Warner, and powers the length delivery past the non-striker, too quick for mid off
pushed towards point
straightish on middle and leg, worked towards midwicket for one

smack! what a shot from Warner, Malinga has been pitching it all the while, Warner winds up and swings it straight back at Malinga who gets a finger to it as he leaps, umpire gets out of the way, Warner gets four, a chance, if you like, strictly theoretical
well bowled, slower at 127 kph from Malinga, slants it fullish and wide, Warner reaches out and thick edges it over point
he tries to belt this one through the off side, but it is even slower at 122 kph, and the shot is mistimed to mid off
swinging into the pads, worked on the leg side

Malinga is now varying his lengths and speeds to Warner, this one is slower from short of a length, Warner does very well to stay in the crease and punch it through extra cover, there is a sliding stop by Tharanga near the rope, but by the time he recovers and throws, they take four
this is a fine contest, Malinga goes for the ripping yorker at 142 kph plus, it is on target, Warner gets feet out of the way and digs it out forcefully

Kula strikes and removes Wade, with Malinga v Warner grabbing all the attention at the other end, gets it to lift and move away from just short of a length, Wade pushes with an angled bat and Sanga takes a neat catch low to his left
straightish length ball some way outside off, left alone
coming in from a good length, he works it awkwardly behind square leg
shaping across Warner from leg stump, he opens up and pats it back to the bowler
worked wide of mid on for one
excellent leave from Ponting, it was pitched up, and moved away instead of coming in, he watched it closely and shouldered arms

furious inswinging yorker from Malinga at 141 kph, it was headed straight for his toes, Warner saved them, he is down on the ground after jabbing the ball to square leg, but he has saved his feet to get up again
now a searing bouncer, Malinga is charged up, Warner gets out of the way hurriedly
another yorker heads for the toes, Warner shuffles, scrambles and somehow manages to get some bat on it, the ball races to fine leg, Warner will be glad to get down to the other end this over

they have got the big one! the old problem returns to haunt Ponting, the front foot was planted a mile across, he had to work a lot to get the bat in front of pad, was late in doing that, by that time the length ball had crashed into the front pad after moving in, would that have gone down leg, the umpire does not think so, replays show it would have just clipped leg stump
the pace is up there at 140.7 kph, it bounces sharply from just short of a length, Clarke leaves immediately
calmly gets across and defends down the track
gets forward neatly to the pitched up ball, reaches out and pushes past extra cover for one
that has come in a mile, that has bounced over the stumps after starting way outside off,  Clarke had let it go already
this time he is ready to defend the one that nips back in
this one goes straightish now, he reaches forward and across and pushes to point
excellent line from Kula, some go straight from just outside off, some scream back in, Clarke sees this one carry straight on and lets it go
Clarke gets hold of this one, Kula pitches it up too full and Clarke uses the incoming angle to lean across and time it through midwicket with a flourish
similar delivery, Clarke drives to mid on crisply
slants it slow, full and wide across Warner, too wide in the end
Warner adjusts well to the 122 kph slower length ball and slices it hard, but point dives to save some runs

that has been timed incredibly well, Malinga goes for that toe-crusher at 142 kph, Warner shuffles a tad and whips it quickly wide of the man at fine leg, who cannot stop the boundary even as he slides across

oh boy, Warner v Malinga it is at the moment all the way, Malinga pitches it up, it is in Warner's slot, he is not entirely in control but he swings at it, and it is fetched from beyond the wide long on boundary
Malinga replies with a superb bouncer, right on target as it heads for Warner's head, he tries to weave away and pull, but is beaten
point saves runs again with a dive to stop a well-timed guide
whips hard as he sees the fuller length coming into the pads, straight to midwicket though
nudged through square leg for a couple
thickish inside edge as he pushes at one nipping in, the ball dribbles square on leg
was shaping up to launch this one over midwicket, but it was short of a good length, and he adjusted to work to midwicket
shaping away after pitching on leg, Warner does not have much room, pats it down the track
times the clip off the pad, and the ball flies in the air wide of mid on who gets around quickly to it
dabbed behind point from the crease
worked in front of square leg
comes across, and brings down one that bounces a tad from just back of a length
gets forward to the pitched up ball and pushes to short cover
very wide one, Clarke reaches out and slaps it through point

Angelo has done what Malinga could not, he has gone through Warner and rattled his stumps, excellent line, angled across the left-hander on a good length, and then nipped back in to sneak in between bat and pad, hit off and middle, Warner was playing the original angle and was done in by the movement, seems that he got an inside edge
pitched up on middle, he defends quietly down the track
pushed towards cover
driven towards mid off
pushed wide of mid off for one
that has to be a very brave leave, that almost took out off stump as it angled across Hussey
gets across and defends back to the bowler
pushed towards covers
length ball bouncing a bit, Clarke is surprised by the lift, and takes a hand off the bat as he drops it on the off side
shaping away a tad but far outside off and left alone
that was pitched up and headed for middle stump, or the pads, Clarke got bat in front of both to work it down to fine leg
thick outside edge now, Angel is troubling them with the bounce from a good length, the ball dribbles past a diving gully
has him reaching out and driving away from the body, the ball is in the air for a bit as it goes to mid off
tries to get the front foot across and drive, but mistimes the stroke back to Angelo
moves forward and blocks one going across him
eases a pitched up ball on the off side, and it takes a dive from Senanayake at extra cover to save runs
pushed to extra cover off the front foot
pushes the pitched up ball on the off side
pushed to cover
moves in towards the leg stump and is worked square with the angle
brilliant stop at cover, they have saved quite a few boundaries today, Clarke had reached out and absolutely smashed this length ball as it straightened outside off
left alone as it angles across outside off
length ball defended towards mid off
pitched up and leaving him with the angle, he looks at it and lets it go
worked off the pads through square leg for two
bounce from a good length again, but going outside off with the angle and left alone

and he beats Clarke first up with a skiddy length ball that holds its line outside off, they all go up for caught behind, Sanga is convinced totally as usual, HotSpot shows nothing on the bat, replays do not indicate any edge
shortish delivery, Clarke pulls it square with the incoming angle, Sri Lanka save another four, brilliant work from Tharanga, getting his right hand in front to stop the ball just inside the rope
Hussey pulls off the front foot, short ball sitting up and he weaves back to crack it in front of square
139.8 kph pitched up ball from Prasad, Hussey pushes to covers
well forward, bends the knee, gets low and defends solidly on the off side
he likes the short ball, he takes a look at it and launches another meaty pull, they have a man at deep midwicket now
some bounce from a good length on off stump, defended down the track
tossed up now, smothered off the front foot
more bounce this time, Hussey drawn forward by the flight, and is surprised as he defends off the splice
chopped to point from the crease
reaches forward to a tossed up full one and pushes to extra cover
ends up on leg stump off the final ball, and is worked square
pitched up ball driven hard off the front foot to mid off
fine shot, Hussey opens the face and drives the length ball through cover, no one's stopping this one
skiddy one angled across and bouncing, left alone
that was full and headed for the pads, Hussey does well to quickly get bat in front and flick it fine
another short ball, another pull from Hussey, deep midwicket comes into play
pitches it up, defended to mid off
worked towards midwicket as he comes across
flighted on middle and leg and turned in front of square
Clarke uses his feet to spin first ball, and pushes back to the bowler
draws him down the track with flight, he eases it back again
fuller one worked to shortish square leg who dives and saves one
Senanayake gets through another tight over, worked to square leg again
gets it to move away and bounce from back  of a length, jabbed away behind point
worked to midwicket who dives and saves more runs
gets forward and across and pushes straight to extra cover
pulled in front of square from back of a length
guided past point for two

Sri Lanka have bettered their brilliance in the field, Kula ups the standards with a leaping blinder, Hussey pushed half-heartedly at a pitched up delivery, it popped in the air down the pitch to Kula's right, the bowler recovered from his followthrough to leap at the ball one-handed and did not let go of it as he landed back on earth
down the track and lofts over extra cover
pushed to long on for one
beaten on the front foot push by one that does not turn much
left alone this time as it bounces outside off
driven towards midwicket
pushes hard down to long on
hurried and opened up by a nippy bouncing length ball, defends on the off side
defends the pitched up ball to point
defends a pitched up ball from the crease
Prasad is on target again with the pitched up ball, Hussey defends tightly to point
some width this time from a good length, and he eases it past cover
gets an inside edge on to pad and back to Prasad as he tries to drive a full one
Clarke deals with the flighted ball with crisp feet, gets to the pitch and smacks it over the bowler
comes down the track again and works the full one towards midwicket
whipped behind square leg for one
backs away and cuts the bouncing delivery, a rare fumble from Sri Lanka, at point, no run conceded though

Tharanga at mid off drops a very tough chance, Senanayake has been tossing it up consistently, and got Hussey to comes forward and push in the air, it just eluded a leaping Tharanga as he got his fingertips to it
more flight, Hussey repeats the shot, with more power, with more conviction and this time Tharanga can watch it go sailing over his head for six over long off
gets behind the line and defends a bouncing delivery down the track
holds its line outside off from a good length, pushed towards cover for a quick run
direct hit would have tested him, whipped across the line to mid on and they charge across for the single, Hussey would have been gone by a foot had the throw hit the stumps
worked behind square on leg
stays in the crease and drops a climbing back of a length ball behind point
width for the cut, he plays the shot, finds point in the way
moves across and forward and smothers a pitched up ball
works a length ball with the angle wide of mid on
left alone outside off
wider outside off, he lets it go again
going on the pads with the angle, tucked to fine leg
digs in the bouncer, does too much with the bounce, way over the batsman's head
appeal for caught behind down the leg side turned down
Hussey starts well after drinks, leans forward in to the length delivery and times the push past a diving extra cover
worked square on the leg side
down leg with the fuller length, superb diving take by Sanga
gets forward and across, drives crisply down to sweeper cover
gets some width as it bounces from short of a length, and pushes out to sweeper cover
defended solidly off the front foot
defends a pitched up ball to mid on
cuts hard but straight to backward point
bit of an inside edge, to midwicket, as he pushes forward
gets the width to launch into another cut, but point leaps to take it one-handed on the bounce
whipped off the pads through square leg
skiddy full one pushed down the track
starts off with a widish length ball moving away from the right-hander, slapped away to cover
very wide from back of a length, he reaches out and slaps it, finds cover again
bouncer at 138 kph, called wide for height
slings it in full and wide outside off, called wide for width this time
gets it right on a good length now, steered to third man
eased to point as he gets forward and across
bouncing from a length, he comes forward and defends solidly to cover
pushed back to the bowler, Malinga coming back well after those wides
pitched up at 124.5 kph, pushed away to point
ending on middle and off, he shuffles across but cannot work past midwicket
thick inside edge through square leg as he pushes hard at a length ball
pushed back to the bowler
he is keeping it full around the stumps, another thick inside edge dribbles behind square leg

superbly timed from Clarke, it seemed a mere work on to the leg side as he came across and turned it through midwicket from outside off, but he had timed it so well that it gave the chasing fielder no chance
scoops a pitched up delivery in the air, just past short extra cover
eased off the front foot, point should have stopped that, considering the high standards Sri Lanka have set today in the field
on the pads, he whips well in the air behind square leg, a slide saves one near the rope

Malinga has broken the stand, leading edge dying on short extra cover, Thirimanne does well to react quickly, goes down to his left to take the catch, David Hussey was looking to turn the length ball on leg
phew, that was brave of Christian in the end, this good length delivery just went over the stumps as it came back in
gets a touch across and defends the pitched up delivery safely

that has to be close, that is worth a long appeal, Sri Lanka put one in, but get nothing out of it, Prasad implores the umpire as this length ball catches Clarke on the pads after nipping back in, could be height, could be going down leg, replays show it would have just gone over leg stump
flails at this one outside off now, and is beaten as it bounces
this time he gets hold of this widish one and cuts past point
pushed to midwicket

another appeal for leg before, skiddy delivery from Prasad, strikes him in front of middle and leg this time, but high on the flap of the pad, replays show it would have just about touched the top of leg, too much doubt with all the bounce on this pitch
pushes the length ball down the track
gets front foot out and defends the length ball
worked to fine leg
eases forward fluidly and dead-bats the length ball on the off side
searing bouncer, Clarke withdraws from the pull and gets head out of the way as it gets big on him at pace
shortish one worked in front of square leg
goes for the yorker around off stump, he pushes it with an inside edge behind square leg
stays in the crease, gets across and defends
neatly done, gets forward and eases the length ball between midwicket and mid on, extremely well timed
well played again, short ball sits up and he swivels to send the pull to the deep square leg boundary
three in a row, through midwicket again, pitched up delivery and for all his power, he shows that he can send them purring along the ground too
left alone outside off
ends the expensive over with another leave
pushed past a diving bowler to long on
gets forward and defends down the pitch
gets forward again and pushes on the off side
whips the full delivery down to long on
smothers the tossed up ball off the front foot
pushed down the track
a run and a diving stop from Mahela at square leg
defended down the track
advances down the track and works towards midwicket, they are not getting the single again
no run again, Christian wanted it after pushing on the off side, Clarke rightly sends him back
gets across and hits down to long on
driven hard down the track
nudged to square leg
forces the bouncing length ball down to long on, similar to the carrom ball, in that it was flicked in
worked through square leg
in the air but falls short of Thirimanne running in from deep midwicket, good effort from the fielder
blocked safely off the front foot
leans back and squeezes out the length ball to point
direct hit from Kula as he races to grab the ball after it is inside edged on the off side, finds the stumps at the non-striker's but Clarke is in
walks across and works from outside off through midwicket
worked straight to mid on from off stump
digs out a full one to mid off
pushes on the up, but straight to extra cover
backs away outside leg and cuts from leg stump, Chandimal throws himself to his left at cover to stop the ball
down the track and lofted over midwicket for a one bounce four, not far from deep midwicket but not close enough for him to have a chance to catch it, he was some way in from the boundary
swept to short fine leg
superb stroke, Christian uses his feet, makes room, and lifts this tossed up ball from off stump over the bowler
worked on the leg side
sends in the bouncer first up down the leg side, Christian misses with the pull, Sanga thinks that is worth an appeal for caught behind
fired in full on leg, dribbles square off the pad
works the full delivery off the pads through square leg
sends in another one close to the blockhole, jammed away
slung widish across the right hander outside off
one more near-yorker, Christian squeezes it out to mid off
moves down the track  but pushes straight back to the bowler, who finds the stumps with a direct hit, Clarke is back safely by then
slower one at 106 kph, he walks across and works it square on leg
well timed, hit powerfully too, but straight to midwicket, moves across and whips the full delivery hard
backs away and looks to pull a bouncer than comes in with the angle, beaten
that is very well played, Clarke brings up a steady 50 with a shuffle outside off, and a nudge to send the full delivery fine down leg from middle
charges out and slogs to long on for a single
whips a full one off middle and leg to deep square leg, that raced across the outfield
attempted full one goes wrong, low full toss down the pads and is it helped fine with a tickle
another low full toss, this time on off, whipped with a thick inside edge in front of square
tries to steer a full delivery some way outside off stump, misses
yorker slung in close to 140 kph, he scrambles to dig it out wide of mid on
bends forward and defends a full one on the off side
worked with the spin to midwicket
ending on middle, worked square on the leg side
worked straight to midwicket again
down the track to the flighted delivery, misses the heave as this one does not turn in, Sanga does not miss the take even as the ball bounces, he hops in the air as he collects and the bails are off
gets across and defends a turning length ball
pushed towards point
worked in front of mid on and Harris lumbers down for the single
turned square on the leg side, they are kept down to one eventually
chopped down to sweeper cover for one

gone! with more than nine overs to go, Mahela takes out Clarke who is furious at getting out, he worked this length ball in the air from middle and Mahela went low to his right quickly to take the catch at midwicket
worked with the angle off the pads in front of square leg
ducks under a short ball
pushed off the front foot to long off
turned to midwicket
opens the face and runs it to backward point
straightening after being angled in from back of a length, was that the flicked carrom ball, pulled to midwicket
Australia continue to lose wickets, the top spinner bounces a lot outside off stump, and Harris cuts it straight to backward point
defended down the track off the front foot
thick outside edge to third man as he pushes from the crease to a pitched up ball
left alone as it carries across him with the angle from a good length
driven hard but straight to extra cover
brings down a climbing back of a length ball off the high part of the bat
drives with an open face, in the air for a while but in the gap past extra cover
punched from the crease to extra cover
beats the edge from around the stumps as Starc pushes inside the line from the crease
tries to force the full one through midwicket but cannot get hold if it
worked in front of square leg
slapped away from the crease to extra cover
angled across from around the wicket, cut to sweeper cover
pushes a length ball to midwicket
short ball close to the head, he top-edges the pull way over Sanga
length ball pushed to cover
pushed wide of midwicket for one
pitched up ball swung down to mid on
goes for another swing, thickish inside edge dribbles through midwicket
thick outside edge this time, well wide of the keeper and Malinga cannot save the boundary from third man
pushes a length ball to point
McKay gets four, goes after the pitched up ball, and cracks it high over wide long off, falls just inside the rope
fuller, and he swings again, this time through midwicket
full toss this time, he backs away and has a go at it, mistimes it to mid on
now he make room and pull a bouncer, cannot make contact

Prasad produces a big outside edge with a skiddy short of a length ball, Sanga takes it in his gloves as he tumbles to his right, but then it pops out, bounces into the ground and lodges back in his gloves, he claimed it initially, but there was some doubt after that, and McKay stays on after the third umpire has a look
very full and just outside off first ball, he jabs at it inside the line
attempted yorker ends up down the pads and is worked crisply through square leg
chipped in the air off the pads, but falls between fine leg and deep square leg
jabs a low full toss down to third man off a thick edge
this one was headed full for middle and leg, but there is no movement and he is able to squeeze it out on the leg side
well done, Malinga tries the slower one on the stumps, he bends forward and blocks safely
drives the pitched up delivery to sweeper cover who keeps them to one
smack! he slogs this full delivery straight down the track, Prasad cannot get to it and the umpire gets out of the way
tries to reach out to a widish one but is beaten
fetches this one from way outside off and mistimes the slog into the leg side
pushes a bouncing back of a length ball close to the bowler on the leg side

taken at long off! Starc tries to clobber the length ball down the ground, ends up slicing it in front of long off, the fielder comes in, misjudges the take initially, but does well to tumble forward and grab it in the end
swings the full delivery down to long on, Dilshan runs in and keeps them to one
driven neatly off the front foot to long off
low full toss hit down to long on for a single
slogged in the air down to long on
gets width with the low full toss and scythes it over extra cover
another low full toss eased down to long on, Australia's tail has batted superbly to take them to the last over. They were eight down in the 42nd

outstanding catch in the deep ends the innings, McKay had backed away, Prasad angled the short ball in, McKay smoked it off the middle of the bat, it seemed headed for six over deep midwicket but Thirimanne came screaming in to his left, and reached out with both hands to pouch the ball just as it was about to sail over the rope, he did well to pull his left hand away from the boundary as he fell down

inn2.comm: wide outside off stump and Tharanga leaves it alone
closer to the off stump this time and Tharanga hangs his bat out at it. He drew the bat back to intentionally play inside the line and it goes through to the keeper
short and wide and Tharanga times the square cut nicely for four
targets the stumps this time, on middle stump and Tharanga pushed it to mid-off
fuller on off stump and Tharanga defends. Harris looking to get it closer to the stumps now
beats him. Pitched on middle and angled away. Tharanga plays and missed, and the ball carries through at a good height to the keeper
pushed across and a bit of swing back in to Dilshan, who goes for a big off drive but does not time it
that one did not swing back and Dilshan is beaten outside off stump. Good bounce from Starc
swinging back into off stump and goes off the inside edge to square leg
that's dropped just short of the keeper. Wide and swinging away from Starc, Tharanga flashes, gets an edge but Wade was standing too far back
beauty from Starc. Pitched on off and swinging away. Tharanga is beaten
full on off stump and Tharanga pushes to mid-off
tucks the length ball with the angle from middle and leg towards midwicket
pushed on the off side from the crease
Dilshan looks to carve this one through the off side, but is beaten as this one bounces from a length
cut straight to Ponting at backward point, not  clean stop but no run conceded
smack! when he misses, he looks suicidal, when he hits, he looks amazing, smacked on the up through extra cover
cannot find the gap with the stroke this time, slightly fuller and he hits it to mid off
squeezes the full delivery with the away movement to extra cover
beats him this time with sharp away shape from a good length

that has been helped straight to Clarke at first slip, Starc strikes early, good delivery, angled in on a good length on off, moving away appreciably, Tharanga is caught on the crease and dabs it high to first slip
that shape away from the great man, Sanga leaves it alone immediately
leans forward to an away going full one and eases it to extra cover
it was only 132.6 kph but it looked much quicker as it zoomed across Dilshan and past his outside edge
excellent line close to off stump with the angle from over the stumps, Sanga lets it go
eases forward and across and thumps the front foot drive straight to cover, boy, was that well timed
worked as it bounces on leg stump, cannot get the single as square leg is around
digs out a full delivery down the track
gets across to a length ball and blocks solidly
four all the way, superb timing again from Sanga as he pushes forward to a pitched up delivery and dispatches it between extra cover and mid off
could have been played on, full and swinging in late, Dilshan tried to force it through the off side, inside edged it on the full, on the bounce to the keeper
half an appeal for leg before, Dilshan misses the work on the leg side, but this one looked to be headed down leg
acrobatic from Wade, it was headed for four byes as it swung down leg but he went leaping full stretch to take it
poor stroke from Dilshan, stays in the crease and tries to hammer this back of a length ball, it moves in again and beats him totally
much better, right forward and smothers the pitched up ball
worked with the movement towards midwicket
gets across and defends
pushes a full delivery off the front foot to mid off
nothing shot from Dilshan, just has a loose and quick waft at one going some way outside off, beaten
tries to hammer the pitched up ball through point, mistimes it to the man
full one pushed wide of mid off for a single
leaves alone a 147 kph length delivery outside off stump
another leave outside off
inside edge dribbles off pad on to leg side as he tries to flick one swinging in full
another full delivery moving in, slammed with lots of bottom hand straight to mid on
crack! too much width for once from Starc, Dilshan plonks front foot out and flays it past extra cover
one more inside edge on to pad as he tries to smack this length delivery through the off side again
pitched up much closer to off now, he defends, for once
Starc lets rip with the yorker, it is handled well in the end as Dilshan collects one with a jab towards third man
play and a miss for the millionth time already from Dilshan to a harmless length delivery outside off
pushed to mid off
absolutely smoked past point, some width for Dilshan and he latches on this time, zero chance for third man
hurried by the short ball into an awkward pull over square leg
left alone outside off
defended down the track
he lets a wide one go past without fiddling with it
pushes well forward and blocks one close to off
short-arm pulls a skiddy shortish one to deep midwicket
well done, big Starc gets quickly down to stop a firm straight push from Sanga
way down the pads but Sanga turns it straight to fine leg
leans forward and pings mid off with a meaty drive
drops a length ball going across, close to the stumps, and looks for the single, there is none
back of a length but on leg, he works it in front of square
midwicket is vacant and Dilshan awkwardly gets the short ball away through that region with a pull
worked wristily from around off in front of square leg
Dilshan lives on, thick outside edge flies wide of slip to the third man boundary as he throws his bat at a length ball
he gets away again, McKay bounces it from just short of a length, and the ball pops up in the air off a surprised Dilshan's bat but well short of point
inside edge races behind square leg as Sanga looks to drive a full one on the off side
misfield from Ponting on the off side allows Dilshan to get away after having backed up too much and also allows a single in the end
pushes a pitched up ball to mid on
steered to third man
gets bat in front of pad to push to midwicket
fine scrambling diving stop by Harris running to his right at mid off, this was four otherwise, Sanga had timed the push really well
moves a long way across and works in front of square leg from outside off
dabs a length ball late down to third man
gets across, stays in the crease and drops this rising delivery towards point
well done, pushes softly down the track and charges across immediately, mid off runs in to pick up the ball but Sanga is home
pushed out to sweeper cover for one
left alone with the angle outside off
cut in the air wide of third man who cannot stop the ball cleanly with the slide, they take two
pushed to mid on for a quick one
guided to point from the crease
there is no slip, and Wade's huge dive cannot get to the flying thick edge from Sanga as he goes after a pitched up delivery
driven to mid off
short, down the leg side, Sanga does not let it go unpunished, he swivels to pull it hard wide of fine leg
dabbed down to third man
defended back to the bowler

gets across and defends the length ball

some discretion from Dilshan as he drops his wrists to a short ball close to him

slapped past a diving point for one

width with the angle from around the stumps, and Chandimal lashes a cut hard into the ground and it bounces well over point to go to the boundary
comes forward to the pitched up ball and pushes to mid off
